raw_meta_yaml:
schema_version: 1

context:
  name: asyncpg
  version: 0.31.0

package:
  name: ${{ name|lower }}
  version: ${{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.org/packages/source/${{ name[0] }}/${{ name }}/${{ name }}-${{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: c989386c83940bfbd787180f2b1519415e2d3d6277a70d9d0f0145ac73500735

build:
  number: 1
  script:
    - if: win
      then: del asyncpg\pgproto\pgproto.c asyncpg\protocol\protocol.c
    - if: unix
      then: rm asyncpg/pgproto/pgproto.c asyncpg/protocol/protocol.c
    - ${{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps -vv

requirements:
  build:
    - if: build_platform != target_platform
      then:
        - python
        - cross-python_${{ target_platform }}
        - cython
    - ${{ compiler('c') }}
    - ${{ stdlib("c") }}
  host:
    - python
    - cython
    - setuptools
    - pip
  run:
    - python
    - async-timeout >=4.0.3

tests:
  - python:
      imports:
        - asyncpg

about:
  license: Apache-2.0
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: A fast PostgreSQL Database Client Library for Python/asyncio.
  description: |
    asyncpg is a database interface library designed specifically for
    PostgreSQL and Python/asyncio. asyncpg is an efficient, clean
    implementation of PostgreSQL server binary protocol for use with Python's
    asyncio framework.
  homepage: https://github.com/MagicStack/asyncpg
  repository: https://github.com/MagicStack/asyncpg
  documentation: https://magicstack.github.io/asyncpg

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - nehaljwani
    - xhochy
